Dr Garba Umar, Adamawa state Commissioner for Information and Strategy, said the newly created Ministry for Entrepreneurship Development was to train and hatch business men to alleviate poverty of the state Umar during his visit to Adamawa office of Correspondents’ Chapel of the Nigeria Union of Journalists’ (NUJ) said, Gov. Ahmadu Fintiri administration, have achieved a lot. He said the declaration of free education and payment of scholarship to student, will support the repositioning of the education system of the state. “The present government, inherited indebted state and saw the urgent need to come up with the ministry as part of measures to address the situation. “Present government met an impoverished people and we are trying to see how we can empower them. “Youths must be gainfully employed or provided with needed skills to gain employment. “The ministry for entrepreneurship, was deliberate created to train and hatch responsible business men and women for the state. “They will be equipped with the needed skills and capacity to come up with proposals that are bankable.” He also said the ministry Construction, Rehabilitation, Intervention and Humanitarian Services to address the challenges faced by IDPs in the state. Alhaji Abdullahi Tukur, chairman of Correspondents’ Chapel, lauded the commissioner for reaching out to the media for support. Tukur who is a state correspondent of FRCN advocated for adverts for his member from the government. 